Three of Mt. Si 2013 Varsity Lacrosse players that recently graduated from Mt. Si High School have started their journey to serve and protect as proud members of the US Military. Cameron Pike and Blake Moorhead (pictured here) are enlisted in the Marines and Matt Mahrer is enlisted in the Navy. All three are currently in boot camp. Their proud parents are all looking forward to celebrating their graduations in the upcoming months.

Cameron Pike and Blake Moorhead graduated from Echo Company 2<sup>nd</sup>Battalion Platoon 2102 on November 15<sup>th</sup>, 2013 at MCRD San Diego. They will be attending the School Of Infantry at Camp Pendleton before being stationed.

